&gt;         If using esnips it has buddy list availability to add other members and you can post your link here when you update and upload new files.  The same goes for storing it on any other file share site. Just post a link and let us know when you upload new files. 
&gt; 
&gt;         I don&#39;t mean to seem anal but I just went thru and cleaned out all the wav files and that alone took up more than 40% of our groups total space. For instance one member has posted about 10 files in mp3 format which didnt even equal 1/4 of the space taken up by another members single wav format file. When it comes down to being 98% full you realize some changes have to be made and this is just one of the many changes this group has had to make to allow more members to join us and have fair access.
&gt; 
&gt;         For those who are posting many files I suggest you do the same because eventually it will come down to one of the mods asking you to do so in order to clear some room. I like the idea of post now then remove after a time period but the truth is that some peoples files need to remain without restraint such as Stefans who has been more than generous to post some files which may come in very handy for some of you to experiment with using his EVPmaker software. These files are for the group as a whole to make use of and they will not be deleted. 
&gt; 
&gt;         That being said, ask for help when you need it and feel free to share with people using the best possible approach for the group as a whole rather than as an individual. When there were only 5 of us here it wasnt a big deal, but once you get past 500 it starts to take a toll and sacrifices must be made. Ive deleted alot of things I didnt wish to and had to ask alot of members who have been around a very long time to help clear some space and they did so willingly for the betterment of the group. They had some really great files too. Most now share them other ways including Sumption who started this group himself. 
